                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d278">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/1773.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Russell</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-10-22T17:00:00-04:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1915—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At present I do not fear developments demanding provision for action as found
                    necessary in Haiti. The only fear is that open rupture between Arias and
                    Velasquez might result in serious situation at capital with the President away.
                    Opposition has induced President to call Congress in extraordinary session for
                    next month to pass measures for the relief of financial situation. Will advise
                    you as soon as decree published.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
